# NexusChat

**An end-to-end agentic Natural-Language-to-SQL engine that turns plain-English business questions into validated, executed, and human-friendly answers — without any hardcoded knowledge of the underlying schema.**


## The 30-Second Pitch

> I designed and built **NexusChat**, a production-style NL2SQL system on the AdventureWorks 2019 database. A user asks a business question in English; the system autonomously discovers the relevant tables, plans a join graph, drafts a T-SQL query, executes it against a live SQL Server, critiques its own result set with an LLM auditor, self-corrects up to 10 times if it detects a business-logic flaw, and finally returns a clean, currency-formatted answer. It's **zero-static** — no schema is hardcoded, it learns the database at setup time and stores everything as a vector knowledge base. I built the full stack myself: the Next.js 16 / React 19 frontend, the FastAPI Python agent, the agentic AI pipeline, the RAG knowledge base, and the Docker-based SQL Server deployment.

