## Why This Project Matters

### The Real-World Problem

Every company sits on a SQL database that only analysts can query. Business users wait days for ad-hoc reports. Existing "text-to-SQL" tools are brittle — they hallucinate joins, sum over-counted columns, or ignore business semantics like "net sales vs. gross revenue". Getting one number wrong in finance reports is unacceptable.

### The Solution

NexusChat treats SQL generation as an **agentic problem**, not a pattern-matching problem. The LLM is wrapped in a closed **Draft → Execute → Audit → Repair** loop that catches its own mistakes by running the query and inspecting the sample results *before* presenting anything to the user. Combined with a RAG-based schema understanding layer, it produces SQL that matches the quality of a senior data analyst — **verified against 12 canonical AdventureWorks analyses from a published benchmark, all correct.**

